# Pre-commit quality gate

Apply when preparing a change for **commit or PR readiness** (or when the user explicitly asks for a quality pass).

**Out of scope:** brainstorming-only messages, pure Q&A, or “explain this file”—unless the user is about to commit those edits.

**Related:** **`AGENTS.md`**; CI mirrors these commands—see **`docs/development-workflow.md`**. Does not replace **`secret-commit-approval-gate`** or **`auth-secrets-safety`**.

## Planning mode

- In planning mode, do not execute validation commands unless the user approves execution.
- Defer this gate to execution mode after explicit approval to run checks.

## Required checks

- `pnpm run lint`
- `pnpm run tsc`
- `pnpm run test` (or `pnpm run test:changed` mid-session; full `test` before merge)
- `pnpm run build` when frontend or server behavior changed

## Documentation gate

When app/config/workflow behavior changes, update:

- `README.md` and/or relevant **`docs/*`** (including **`docs/styleguide/`** when patterns shift)
- **`CHANGELOG.md`** under **`## [Unreleased]`**
- **`docs/plans/*.md`** when a committed planning artifact is part of the change

**Large PRs:** post-merge pass per **`docs/styleguide/frontend-patterns.md`** and **`docs/styleguide/backend-patterns.md`**.

## Database gate

If **`server/db/schema.ts`** or **`database/schema.sql`** changes:

- Add migrations under **`database/migrations/`** and update **`database/migrations/meta/_journal.json`** (and snapshots if used)
- Keep Drizzle and SQL mirror in parity

## Deployment / auth safety

For auth or deploy changes, update **`docs/configuration.md`** and **`docs/deployment/README.md`** (and add provider-specific docs when OIDC lands).
